Description: mEYFP is a basic (constitutively fluorescent) yellow fluorescent protein published in 2002, derived from Aequorea victoria. It is reported to be a very rapidly-maturing monomer.
mRuby2 is a basic (constitutively fluorescent) red fluorescent protein published in 2012, derived from Entacmaea quadricolor. It has moderate acid sensitivity.
